TITLE: Ordering and Grouping in Sequelize
DESCRIPTION: Shows various ways to implement ORDER BY clauses in Sequelize queries, including ordering by columns, functions, and associated models.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sequelize/website/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-6.x.x/core-concepts/model-querying-basics.md#2025-04-09_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
Subtask.findAll({
  order: [
    ['title', 'DESC'],
    sequelize.fn('max', sequelize.col('age')),
    [sequelize.fn('max', sequelize.col('age')), 'DESC'],
    [sequelize.fn('otherfunction', sequelize.col('col1'), 12, 'lalala'), 'DESC'],
    [Task, 'createdAt', 'DESC'],
    [Task, Project, 'createdAt', 'DESC'],
    ['Task', 'createdAt', 'DESC'],
    ['Task', 'Project', 'createdAt', 'DESC'],
    [Subtask.associations.Task, 'createdAt', 'DESC'],
    [Subtask.associations.Task, Task.associations.Project, 'createdAt', 'DESC'],
    [{ model: Task, as: 'Task' }, 'createdAt', 'DESC'],
    [{ model: Task, as: 'Task' }, { model: Project, as: 'Project' }, 'createdAt', 'DESC']
  ]
});
```

