TITLE: Implementing Limits and Pagination with Sequelize
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use limit and offset options for pagination in Sequelize queries. These options control how many records to fetch and how many to skip.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sequelize/website/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-6.x.x/core-concepts/model-querying-basics.md#2025-04-09_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Fetch 10 instances/rows
Project.findAll({ limit: 10 });

// Skip 8 instances/rows
Project.findAll({ offset: 8 });

// Skip 5 instances and fetch the 5 after that
Project.findAll({ offset: 5, limit: 5 });
```

