TITLE: Finding or Creating a User in Sequelize with JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the use of the findOrCreate method to either find an existing user or create a new one if not found. It shows how to set up the where and defaults options, and how to handle the returned values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sequelize/website/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-6.x.x/core-concepts/model-querying-finders.md#2025-04-09_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const [user, created] = await User.findOrCreate({
  where: { username: 'sdepold' },
  defaults: {
    job: 'Technical Lead JavaScript',
  },
});
console.log(user.username); // 'sdepold'
console.log(user.job); // This may or may not be 'Technical Lead JavaScript'
console.log(created); // The boolean indicating whether this instance was just created
if (created) {
  console.log(user.job); // This will certainly be 'Technical Lead JavaScript'
}
```

