TITLE: Defining Sequelize Model Using TypeScript Class Extension
DESCRIPTION: Example of extending Model class in TypeScript with type inference and attribute definitions. Shows how to define a User model with id, firstName, and lastName fields using the Model.init() method.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sequelize/website/blob/main/docs/other-topics/legacy-model-definitions.mdx#2025-04-09_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import {
  Sequelize,
  DataTypes,
  Model,
  InferAttributes,
  InferCreationAttributes,
  CreationOptional,
} from '@sequelize/core';
import { SqliteDialect } from '@sequelize/sqlite3';

const sequelize = new Sequelize({ dialect: SqliteDialect });

class User extends Model<InferAttributes<User>, InferCreationAttributes<User>> {
  declare id: CreationOptional<number>;
  declare firstName: string;
  declare lastName: string | null;
}

User.init(
  {
    id: {
      type: DataTypes.INTEGER,
      autoIncrement: true,
      primaryKey: true,
    },
    firstName: {
      type: DataTypes.STRING,
      allowNull: false,
    },
    lastName: {
      type: DataTypes.STRING,
    },
  },
  {
    sequelize,
  }
);
```

