TITLE: Combining Getter and Setter for Content Compression in Sequelize
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to combine a getter and setter to implement content compression for a Post model in Sequelize. The content is compressed before storage and decompressed when accessed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sequelize/website/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-6.x.x/core-concepts/getters-setters-virtuals.md#2025-04-09_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const { gzipSync, gunzipSync } = require('zlib');

const Post = sequelize.define('post', {
  content: {
    type: DataTypes.TEXT,
    get() {
      const storedValue = this.getDataValue('content');
      const gzippedBuffer = Buffer.from(storedValue, 'base64');
      const unzippedBuffer = gunzipSync(gzippedBuffer);
      return unzippedBuffer.toString();
    },
    set(value) {
      const gzippedBuffer = gzipSync(value);
      this.setDataValue('content', gzippedBuffer.toString('base64'));
    },
  },
});
```

