TITLE: Using hooks with transactions in Sequelize
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to access and reuse the transaction object within a hook function. This ensures that database operations in hooks use the same transaction as the operation that triggered the hook.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sequelize/website/blob/main/docs/other-topics/hooks.mdx#2025-04-09_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
User.hooks.addListener('afterCreate', async (user, options) => {
  // We can use `options.transaction` to perform some other call
  // using the same transaction of the call that triggered this hook
  await User.update(
    { mood: 'sad' },
    {
      where: {
        id: user.id,
      },
      transaction: options.transaction,
    },
  );
});

await sequelize.transaction(async transaction => {
  await User.create(
    {
      username: 'someguy',
      mood: 'happy',
    },
    {
      transaction,
    },
  );
});
